        "attrs": {
          "id": null,
          "pairs": {
            "- matcher": "\"Write\"",
            "- type": "command",
            "PreToolUse": "",
            "allowed-tools": "",
            "command": "\"bash ${CLAUDE_SKILL_DIR}/bin/check-freeze.sh\"",
            "description": "|",
            "hooks": "",
            "name": "freeze",
            "statusMessage": "\"Checking freeze boundary...\"",
            "version": "0.1.0"
          }
        },
        "title": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "text": "/freeze â€” Restrict Edits to a Directory"
          }
        ],
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "Text",
            "text": "<!-- AUTO-GENERATED from SKILL.md.tmpl â€” do not edit directly -->\n<!-- Regenerate: bun run gen:skill-docs -->\n\n\nLock file edits to a specific directory. Any Edit or Write operation targeting\na file outside the allowed path will be **blocked** (not just warned).\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.gstack/analytics\necho '{\"skill\":\"freeze\",\"ts\":\"'$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ)'\",\"repo\":\"'$(basename \"$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel 2>/dev/null)\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")'\"}'  >> ~/.gstack/analytics/skill-usage.jsonl 2>/dev/null || true\n```"
          }
        ],
        "children": [
          {
            "kind": {
              "type": "Section",
              "attrs": {
                "id": null,
                "pairs": {}
              },
              "title": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "text": "Setup"
                }
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "kind": {
                    "type": "Paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "Text",
                        "text": "Ask the user which directory to restrict edits to. Use AskUserQuestion:\n\n- Question: \"Which directory should I restrict edits to? Files outside this path will be blocked from editing.\"\n- Text input (not multiple choice) â€” the user types a path.\n\nOnce the user provides a directory path:\n\n1. Resolve it to an absolute path:\n```bash\nFREEZE_DIR=$(cd \"<user-provided-path>\" 2>/dev/null && pwd)\necho \"$FREEZE_DIR\"\n```\n\n2. Ensure trailing slash and save to the freeze state file:\n```bash\nFREEZE_DIR=\"${FREEZE_DIR%/}/\"\nSTATE_DIR=\"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_DATA:-$HOME/.gstack}\"\nmkdir -p \"$STATE_DIR\"\necho \"$FREEZE_DIR\" > \"$STATE_DIR/freeze-dir.txt\"\necho \"Freeze boundary set: $FREEZE_DIR\"\n```\n\nTell the user: \"Edits are now restricted to `<path>/`. Any Edit or Write\noutside this directory will be blocked. To change the boundary, run `/freeze`\nagain. To remove it, run `/unfreeze` or end the session.\""
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "span": {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 0
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "span": {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 0
            }
          },
          {
            "kind": {
              "type": "Section",
              "attrs": {
                "id": null,
                "pairs": {}
              },
              "title": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "text": "How it works"
                }
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "kind": {
                    "type": "Paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "Text",
                        "text": "The hook reads `file_path` from the Edit/Write tool input JSON, then checks\nwhether the path starts with the freeze directory. If not, it returns\n`permissionDecision: \"deny\"` to block the operation.\n\nThe freeze boundary persists for the session via the state file. The hook\nscript reads it on every Edit/Write invocation."
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "span": {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 0
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "span": {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 0
            }
          },
          {
            "kind": {
              "type": "Section",
              "attrs": {
                "id": null,
                "pairs": {}
              },
              "title": [
                {
                  "type": "Text",
                  "text": "Notes"
                }
              ],
              "children": [
                {
                  "kind": {
                    "type": "Paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "Text",
                        "text": "- The trailing `/` on the freeze directory prevents `/src` from matching `/src-old`\n- Freeze applies to Edit and Write tools only â€” Read, Bash, Glob, Grep are unaffected\n- This prevents accidental edits, not a security boundary â€” Bash commands like `sed` can still modify files outside the boundary\n- To deactivate, run `/unfreeze` or end the conversation"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  "span": {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 0
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            "span": {
              "start": 0,
              "end": 0
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      "span": {
        "start": 0,
        "end": 0
      }
    }
  ]
}